1. Circle's US IPO stock offering price is expected to be set at $31 per share, with a financing scale of $1.1 billion;
2. JPMorgan Chase plans to accept cryptocurrency ETFs as loan collateral;
3. Market news: US SEC postpones decision on Canary spot SUI ETF application;
4. Trump: Debt ceiling should be completely lifted to avoid economic disaster;
5. Ethereum Foundation releases latest fiscal policy, emphasizing "Defipunk" concept and privacy protection;
6. SEC formally accepts Nasdaq 21Shares SUI ETF listing application;
7. CLARITY bill review is blocked, Trump's cryptocurrency activities spark controversy in the House of Representatives;
8. K-Pop media company K Wave announces Bitcoin strategy, stock price soars 130%;
9. California passes bill allowing confiscation of "idle" cryptocurrencies;
10. US M2 money supply has reached $21.86 trillion, a record high;
11. TRUMP Wallet X account has been unfrozen.
